CatDescriptText: Jacqueline Staten, 2020 Wylie Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1958, pg. 6 with question: "Do you believe the trouble in Middle East will start an atomic world war?" answer reads: "I believe so. The way things look now, I think we will have a war."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Jacqueline Staten, wearing earrings and button down dress with pom pom tie at collar, standing in front of grocery store cooler with boxes of "Velveeta", "Old English", and "Chateau", possibly Thorofare Market
